A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Chapter 2 of Title 20 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
2 elementary and secondary education, so as to provide for free meals to public school students
3 enrolled in after-school education programs or summer school education programs; to
4 provide for policies, rules, and regulations; to provide for related matters; to provide a short
5 title; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 This Act shall be known and may be cited as the "Leave No Georgia Child Hungry Act."
9 SECTION 2.
10 Chapter 2 of Title 20 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to elementary and
11 secondary education, is amended in Part 5 of Article 6, relating to program weights and
12 funding requirements, by adding a new Code section to read as follows:
13 "20-2-187.1.
14 (a)(1) The State Board of Education shall annually determine the amount of state funds
15 needed to provide a state-wide program to offer quality and healthy meals, without
