16 charge, to all students enrolled in a public school in this state who are enrolled in
17 after-school education programs or summer school education programs. State funds
18 appropriated for this purpose shall be used to supplement federal funds, if any.
19 (2) The State Board of Education shall promulgate rules and regulations which:
20 (A) Establish minimum nutritional requirements for after-school meal programs and
21 summer school meal programs which meet or exceed the minimum federal regulations;
22 (B) Provide that each participating local school system submit a plan of compliance;
23 and
24 (C) Assist local school systems in applying for and obtaining start-up grant money for
25 such programs.
26 (b) Each local school system is encouraged to establish and support a program to offer
27 quality and healthy meals, without charge, to all students enrolled in a public school in this
28 state who are enrolled in after-school education programs or summer school education
29 programs. Each local education school system operating such a program shall be
30 reimbursed by the state according to policies, rules, and regulations established by the State
31 Board of Education and subject to appropriations for such purposes by the General
32 Assembly."
33 SECTION 3.
34 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
